1
00:00:32,931 --> 00:00:34,700
(A new teacher)

2
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:37,140
(North Pole Teacher)

3
00:00:37,141 --> 00:00:38,440
You know the lines, right?

4
00:00:38,441 --> 00:00:41,470
(The 1st class as a team of 3...)

5
00:00:41,471 --> 00:00:44,081
(wasn't easy.)

6
00:00:44,511 --> 00:00:46,711
(This is tough.)

7
00:00:47,511 --> 00:00:49,981
(Today's homework: Memorize the script)

8
00:00:50,621 --> 00:00:53,751
(Will they be able to perform without the script next time?)

9
00:00:54,451 --> 00:00:57,061
(The long-awaited music director, CO KUN, has arrived.)

10
00:00:59,091 --> 00:01:02,030
(The music they waited for is perfect!)

11
00:01:02,031 --> 00:01:03,031
With footsteps.

12
00:01:04,061 --> 00:01:07,231
(The music and sound effects will be completed with the kids.)

13
00:01:07,901 --> 00:01:10,601
(TPNC has finally come together.)

14
00:01:11,271 --> 00:01:14,111
(The 4 teachers' 1st night together was filled with laughter.)

15
00:01:20,351 --> 00:01:24,251
(Sunday morning filled with the scent of rain)

16
00:01:26,021 --> 00:01:28,921
(Tae Ri is still sound asleep.)

17
00:01:32,861 --> 00:01:34,631
(Getting up)

18
00:01:42,571 --> 00:01:46,471
(His sleeping pose is quite artistic.)

19
00:01:48,311 --> 00:01:52,011
(He looks artistic too.)

20
00:01:55,581 --> 00:01:58,151
(Startled)

21
00:02:00,051 --> 00:02:02,691
(Things seem quite awkward.)

22
00:02:03,051 --> 00:02:04,720
Why are you sleeping over there?

23
00:02:04,721 --> 00:02:06,590
I must've felt hot and ended up sleeping down here.

24
00:02:06,591 --> 00:02:07,761
- Is that so?
-  Yes.

25
00:02:09,331 --> 00:02:10,401
You startled me.

26
00:02:11,561 --> 00:02:14,170
I had the weirdest dream.

27
00:02:14,171 --> 00:02:15,231
What was it about?

28
00:02:16,131 --> 00:02:18,601
All the senior entertainers showed up.

29
00:02:20,311 --> 00:02:21,471
For real.

30
00:02:21,971 --> 00:02:23,481
From Yu Jae Seok...

31
00:02:23,941 --> 00:02:25,541
to Lee Kyung Sil.

32
00:02:26,751 --> 00:02:27,811
I'm serious.

33
00:02:28,081 --> 00:02:30,550
- Everyone was gathered together.
-  Why'd you have such a dream?

34
00:02:30,551 --> 00:02:33,121
(The rookie entertainer dreams of other entertainers.)

35
00:02:36,351 --> 00:02:40,031
(After waking up, they make their beds first.)

36
00:02:41,291 --> 00:02:43,361
(Smiling)

37
00:02:46,231 --> 00:02:49,001
(The Running Lover runs even today.)

38
00:02:49,531 --> 00:02:51,001
Why am I the only one gaining weight?

39
00:02:53,541 --> 00:02:56,711
I don't understand. Nobody else is getting fat.

40
00:02:57,481 --> 00:02:58,811
Why do I get all puffy?

41
00:03:01,451 --> 00:03:02,911
Well, it's because I ate a ton.

42
00:03:04,281 --> 00:03:05,480
That's the only reason.

43
00:03:05,481 --> 00:03:07,020
I ate too much.

44
00:03:07,021 --> 00:03:08,521
(The humanization of self-reflection)

45
00:03:11,391 --> 00:03:12,461
It smells good.

46
00:03:12,761 --> 00:03:14,361
Hold on. Try smelling this.

47
00:03:15,831 --> 00:03:17,960
This is the scent we're used to.

48
00:03:17,961 --> 00:03:19,971
(Barista KUN is in the Mushroom House.)

49
00:03:20,101 --> 00:03:22,331
And this is the scent of good coffee beans.

50
00:03:24,501 --> 00:03:26,871
Should I say it smells floral?

51
00:03:27,911 --> 00:03:30,281
You like coffee because it's like music, don't you?

52
00:03:32,281 --> 00:03:33,811
- The two have a lot in common.
-  I see.

53
00:03:36,051 --> 00:03:37,420
(Barista KUN's pour-over coffee)

54
00:03:37,421 --> 00:03:38,821
I'm not sure if you'll like it.

55
00:03:39,821 --> 00:03:42,291
- That's a small amount of coffee.
-  Right?

56
00:03:42,891 --> 00:03:45,161
I always thought bland meant less coffee...

57
00:03:45,461 --> 00:03:47,831
and strong meant more coffee.

58
00:03:48,131 --> 00:03:49,261
No, never.

59
00:03:49,591 --> 00:03:51,761
- Never?
-  The richness of coffee.

60
00:03:51,931 --> 00:03:54,471
The intensity and richness of coffee...

61
00:03:55,631 --> 00:03:57,800
have to do with the temperature of the water.

62
00:03:57,801 --> 00:03:59,071
(Said by Barista KUN)

63
00:03:59,671 --> 00:04:01,211
(Drinking)

64
00:04:05,341 --> 00:04:06,951
It tastes out of this world.

65
00:04:09,051 --> 00:04:10,220
Is there no need to pour water...

66
00:04:10,221 --> 00:04:11,381
- around it?
-  No.

67
00:04:11,751 --> 00:04:12,920
No?

68
00:04:12,921 --> 00:04:14,891
The coffee ends up with an unpleasant aftertaste.

69
00:04:15,721 --> 00:04:16,990
- Unpleasant...
-  Unpleasant aftertaste.

70
00:04:16,991 --> 00:04:18,061
"Unpleasant aftertaste."

71
00:04:19,161 --> 00:04:20,630
- Because of the filter?
-  Yes.

72
00:04:20,631 --> 00:04:23,900
That prevents the coffee from having an aromatic smell.

73
00:04:23,901 --> 00:04:25,301
(The curious customer and friendly Barista KUN)

74
00:04:26,331 --> 00:04:28,100
(Drinking it iced this time)

75
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:29,171
Not bad.

76
00:04:30,301 --> 00:04:31,541
It's much more sour.

77
00:04:33,001 --> 00:04:35,611
Make it into iced coffee, and it turns into juice.

78
00:04:37,181 --> 00:04:38,241
It's...

79
00:04:38,881 --> 00:04:40,151
not my style.

80
00:04:40,481 --> 00:04:41,851
I need to dilute it more.

81
00:04:42,511 --> 00:04:44,250
It needs more water.

82
00:04:44,251 --> 00:04:45,281
- Is that so?
-  Yes.

83
00:04:45,951 --> 00:04:47,020
"Dilute."

84
00:04:47,021 --> 00:04:48,791
I wasn't sure what you meant by that.

85
00:04:49,591 --> 00:04:52,691
Adding more water will make it more enjoyable.

86
00:04:55,631 --> 00:04:57,501
(Sipping)

87
00:05:01,601 --> 00:05:03,501
- It's good.
-  Right?

88
00:05:06,201 --> 00:05:10,441
(Having morning coffee together with Barista KUN)

89
00:05:12,011 --> 00:05:14,011
Kangnam should wake up soon.

90
00:05:15,011 --> 00:05:16,211
We should check...

91
00:05:17,081 --> 00:05:18,251
if he's alive or not.

92
00:05:21,791 --> 00:05:24,721
(Cut out for the caravan, not moving an inch)

93
00:05:25,361 --> 00:05:26,761
(Knocking)

94
00:05:29,731 --> 00:05:31,201
- Kangnam.
-  Yes?

95
00:05:31,961 --> 00:05:34,171
It's time for you to wake up.

96
00:05:35,371 --> 00:05:36,400
Got it.

97
00:05:36,401 --> 00:05:37,841
- Come out, okay?
-  Okay.

98
00:05:40,311 --> 00:05:43,681
(Everyone is awake now.)

99
00:05:43,811 --> 00:05:45,210
- Okay.
-  Okay.

100
00:05:45,211 --> 00:05:46,381
Shall we get going now?

101
00:05:48,581 --> 00:05:51,251
(Today's weather: Strong winds)

102
00:05:52,521 --> 00:05:54,620
It's a tornado!

103
00:05:54,621 --> 00:05:56,921
Dorothy's house is going to fly away.

104
00:05:57,321 --> 00:05:59,860
- When's Ms. Kim coming?
-  I want to pick apples already.

105
00:05:59,861 --> 00:06:01,091
(Where are the students waiting for the teachers?)

106
00:06:02,991 --> 00:06:06,331
(A vast apple orchard)

107
00:06:06,931 --> 00:06:07,971
How big.

108
00:06:08,501 --> 00:06:10,001
- It's huge.
-  Right?

109
00:06:10,801 --> 00:06:11,871
It's red over here.

110
00:06:12,471 --> 00:06:13,641
This one is big.

111
00:06:13,841 --> 00:06:15,341
- How pretty.
-  The trees are so tall.

112
00:06:17,481 --> 00:06:19,010
(During the fourth class)

113
00:06:19,011 --> 00:06:21,011
- Hi.
-  Hello.

114
00:06:21,451 --> 00:06:22,551
You see...

115
00:06:22,751 --> 00:06:25,021
Would you like to visit our apple orchard?

116
00:06:25,321 --> 00:06:26,821
Yes, we'd love to.

117
00:06:27,221 --> 00:06:28,551
Are you inviting us over?

118
00:06:29,151 --> 00:06:30,991
- Thank you, Ju Eun.
-  No problem.

119
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,930
- Hi.
-  Hi.

120
00:06:33,931 --> 00:06:35,330
- Gosh.
-  Ju Eun.

121
00:06:35,331 --> 00:06:36,690
I'm Ju Eun's mom.

122
00:06:36,691 --> 00:06:39,061
- Hi.
-  Hi.

123
00:06:39,431 --> 00:06:41,771
Your apple orchard is huge, Ju Eun.

124
00:06:41,871 --> 00:06:43,500
We heard we could pick...

125
00:06:43,501 --> 00:06:45,401
- some apples today.
-  That's right.

126
00:06:45,601 --> 00:06:46,670
The kids know...

127
00:06:46,671 --> 00:06:47,671
- how to pick them, right?
-  Yes.

128
00:06:47,672 --> 00:06:48,970
- Let's ask the kids.
-  Go ahead.

129
00:06:48,971 --> 00:06:50,280
- Even better.
-  Yes, even better.

130
00:06:50,281 --> 00:06:52,540
The students could become teachers one day.

131
00:06:52,541 --> 00:06:53,950
Exactly.

132
00:06:53,951 --> 00:06:55,781
- Why don't we get going?
-  Okay, this way.

133
00:06:55,881 --> 00:06:58,281
- Let's go.
-  Go!

134
00:06:59,481 --> 00:07:01,421
Ju Eun, how do you pick the apples up there?

135
00:07:02,191 --> 00:07:03,191
Using the ladder.

136
00:07:03,192 --> 00:07:04,891
Using a ladder, not shaking the tree?

137
00:07:05,221 --> 00:07:07,090
That'll bruise the apples.

138
00:07:07,091 --> 00:07:08,931
The apples will get bruised.

139
00:07:09,291 --> 00:07:11,800
- That didn't cross my mind.
-  We can't bruise the apples.

140
00:07:11,801 --> 00:07:13,500
No, we can't.

141
00:07:13,501 --> 00:07:14,871
She's an apple expert.

142
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:17,671
How much is it per square meter?

143
00:07:18,171 --> 00:07:19,201
Well...

144
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:22,210
It's just that huge.

145
00:07:22,211 --> 00:07:23,610
- I'm shocked.
-  If it's this big...

146
00:07:23,611 --> 00:07:24,781
You're a rich landowner.

147
00:07:25,681 --> 00:07:27,050
- Won Jin.
-  Won Jin.

148
00:07:27,051 --> 00:07:28,450
- Won Jin!
-  You scared me.

149
00:07:28,451 --> 00:07:29,981
- You look like the owner.
-  Come over here.

150
00:07:30,181 --> 00:07:31,950
- Come.
-  He does look like the owner.

151
00:07:31,951 --> 00:07:33,351
- Gosh.
-  Hurry.

152
00:07:34,691 --> 00:07:35,691
You're finally here.

153
00:07:35,691 --> 00:07:36,691
- Won Jin.
-  How cute.

154
00:07:36,692 --> 00:07:37,960
- Hey, guys.
-  Hi.

155
00:07:37,961 --> 00:07:39,760
- Hi.
-  Hi.

156
00:07:39,761 --> 00:07:41,260
- There are a lot of apples, right?
-  Hi.

157
00:07:41,261 --> 00:07:42,330
- There are tons.
-  Hi.

158
00:07:42,331 --> 00:07:43,561
- Introduce him.
-  Hi.

159
00:07:44,431 --> 00:07:45,860
- Do you know me?
-  I've seen you before.

160
00:07:45,861 --> 00:07:46,901
He knows him.

161
00:07:47,271 --> 00:07:48,830
Do you know me? Have you seen me somewhere?

162
00:07:48,831 --> 00:07:50,000
Have you seen him somewhere?

163
00:07:50,001 --> 00:07:52,570
- A celebrity has finally come!
-  Right?

164
00:07:52,571 --> 00:07:53,940
- I'm a celebrity, right?
-  Do you know him?

165
00:07:53,941 --> 00:07:55,370
- Yes.
-  You do?

166
00:07:55,371 --> 00:07:56,440
The celebrity you've been waiting for is here.

167
00:07:56,441 --> 00:07:58,540
- What about me? Right?
-  You're a celebrity.

168
00:07:58,541 --> 00:08:00,180
Their reactions are different from when I came.

169
00:08:00,181 --> 00:08:01,181
(Upset)

170
00:08:01,681 --> 00:08:04,420
Guys, don't you see an unfamiliar face among us today?

171
00:08:04,421 --> 00:08:05,820
- Yes.
-  Right?

172
00:08:05,821 --> 00:08:07,190
Do you know who he is?

173
00:08:07,191 --> 00:08:08,391
"I Live Alone."

174
00:08:09,651 --> 00:08:11,220
- "I Live Alone." - "I Live Alone."

175
00:08:11,221 --> 00:08:12,560
- He was in "I Live Alone." - "I Live Alone" is powerful.

176
00:08:12,561 --> 00:08:13,561
An autograph, please.

177
00:08:13,562 --> 00:08:15,491
- All right.
-  The kids are happy to see him.

178
00:08:15,931 --> 00:08:17,700
- An autograph, please.
-  Where have you seen him?

179
00:08:17,701 --> 00:08:20,131
We need a nickname for him. What should it be?

180
00:08:20,331 --> 00:08:21,870
You can call me Mr. CO KUN...

181
00:08:21,871 --> 00:08:23,171
or Mr. CO.

182
00:08:23,671 --> 00:08:25,240
- How about Mr. CO?
-  How about it?

183
00:08:25,241 --> 00:08:27,070
- Mr. CO.
-  Let's go with Mr. CO.

184
00:08:27,071 --> 00:08:29,341
Guys, let's all greet Mr. CO together.

185
00:08:29,541 --> 00:08:31,080
- Hi, Mr. CO.
-  Hi.

186
00:08:31,081 --> 00:08:33,011
- Hi.
-  Hi.

187
00:08:33,181 --> 00:08:34,580
(A celebrity's attitude)

188
00:08:34,581 --> 00:08:37,280
We've got four teachers now.

189
00:08:37,281 --> 00:08:38,650
- That's right.
-  Yes.

190
00:08:38,651 --> 00:08:40,390
The acting class...

191
00:08:40,391 --> 00:08:41,620
- has four teachers now.
-  Four, right?

192
00:08:41,621 --> 00:08:42,990
- You have four teachers.
-  Yes.

193
00:08:42,991 --> 00:08:44,490
- We might continue.
-  Shall we?

194
00:08:44,491 --> 00:08:45,590
Do you want to try this on, Ha Yun?

195
00:08:45,591 --> 00:08:46,721
- What?
-  We can see that.

196
00:08:47,131 --> 00:08:49,960
We need to pick apples today. Do you know how to do it?

197
00:08:49,961 --> 00:08:51,101
- Yes.
-  Yes.

198
00:08:51,201 --> 00:08:52,300
- Tell us.
-  We're the only ones unaware.

199
00:08:52,301 --> 00:08:54,200
- You don't?
-  Grab one like this,

200
00:08:54,201 --> 00:08:56,370
- and twist it.
-  Do you not use scissors?

201
00:08:56,371 --> 00:08:58,841
- No.
-  You can use scissors.

202
00:08:59,101 --> 00:09:00,470
Twist and pull.

203
00:09:00,471 --> 00:09:02,771
- Twist and pull.
-  Twist and pull.

204
00:09:02,871 --> 00:09:04,240
Shinano Gold, Gamhong, and Fuji.

205
00:09:04,241 --> 00:09:05,380
What? Sorry?

206
00:09:05,381 --> 00:09:06,680
Shinano Gold, Gamhong, and Fuji.

207
00:09:06,681 --> 00:09:07,811
What? Sorry?

208
00:09:08,281 --> 00:09:10,250
- Tsugaru.
-  The types of apples?

209
00:09:10,251 --> 00:09:11,280
- Apples.
-  Tsugaru.

210
00:09:11,281 --> 00:09:12,480
- The apples.
-  Are there...

211
00:09:12,481 --> 00:09:14,190
- many types of apples here?
-  Yes.

212
00:09:14,191 --> 00:09:15,420
Summer King. Most of them...

213
00:09:15,421 --> 00:09:17,090
- are Fuji apples.
-  What's here?

214
00:09:17,091 --> 00:09:19,561
- Muji?
-  Fuji.

215
00:09:19,791 --> 00:09:20,990
Most of them are Fuji apples.

216
00:09:20,991 --> 00:09:22,631
We've got a handful of apple experts here.

217
00:09:22,891 --> 00:09:25,501
Guide us well. We don't know how to do it.

218
00:09:25,701 --> 00:09:27,030
- Okay.
-  Good.

219
00:09:27,031 --> 00:09:31,041
Guys, let's split into teams and compete.

220
00:09:31,101 --> 00:09:32,570
- I'm in.
-  We'll split into teams...

221
00:09:32,571 --> 00:09:34,710
and compete to see who can pick the most apples.

222
00:09:34,711 --> 00:09:38,041
Okay, which teacher was here the longest?

223
00:09:38,481 --> 00:09:39,680
- Ms. Kim.
-  Ms. Kim...

224
00:09:39,681 --> 00:09:41,150
- and Mr. Choi, right?
-  Potato Teacher.

225
00:09:41,151 --> 00:09:42,180
- Potato Teacher, right?
-  Yes.

226
00:09:42,181 --> 00:09:43,950
The two will stand side by side.

227
00:09:43,951 --> 00:09:48,650
We will line up behind the leader...

228
00:09:48,651 --> 00:09:50,121
we want to be on a team with.

229
00:09:50,291 --> 00:09:51,660
- Potato Teacher or Ms. Kim.
-  No.

230
00:09:51,661 --> 00:09:53,760
- Take your time.
-  Line up.

231
00:09:53,761 --> 00:09:55,791
- I can't decide.
-  Hey.

232
00:09:56,291 --> 00:09:57,300
- Ha Yun.
-  Yes?

233
00:09:57,301 --> 00:09:58,900
Don't you want to be a team with me?

234
00:09:58,901 --> 00:10:00,300
- No.
-  What?

235
00:10:00,301 --> 00:10:02,471
- Don't you?
-  No.

236
00:10:02,871 --> 00:10:05,101
- All right.
-  I'm okay.

237
00:10:05,301 --> 00:10:06,640
- Do we line up too?
-  Yes.

238
00:10:06,641 --> 00:10:07,670
We have to line up too.

239
00:10:07,671 --> 00:10:09,671
- Us too?
-  Yes. Stand facing forward.

240
00:10:10,311 --> 00:10:13,650
You'll be able to tell which teacher is the students' favorite.

241
00:10:13,651 --> 00:10:14,880
Today was supposed to be easygoing.

242
00:10:14,881 --> 00:10:16,010
- Right.
-  Whatever.

243
00:10:16,011 --> 00:10:17,581
- The respect you've earned so far.
-  No?

244
00:10:18,181 --> 00:10:21,451
Line up behind the teacher you like more, okay?

245
00:10:22,321 --> 00:10:23,321
Go.

246
00:10:23,791 --> 00:10:25,420
- Please be sincere about it.
-  Over here.

247
00:10:25,421 --> 00:10:27,991
What color jacket am I wearing today? Apple red, right?

248
00:10:28,731 --> 00:10:30,160
- Okay.
-  I'm good at picking apples.

249
00:10:30,161 --> 00:10:31,200
From what I see,

250
00:10:31,201 --> 00:10:33,330
one teacher is going to get hurt.

251
00:10:33,331 --> 00:10:35,570
(Already a bad feeling someone will get hurt)

252
00:10:35,571 --> 00:10:37,340
- I'm wearing apple red today.
-  Oh, dear.

253
00:10:37,341 --> 00:10:38,901
Gosh, I feel bad.

254
00:10:39,401 --> 00:10:40,740
I can't watch it.

255
00:10:40,741 --> 00:10:41,871
(Let me look away.)

256
00:10:42,271 --> 00:10:43,311
I can't...

257
00:10:44,281 --> 00:10:45,740
Gosh, I feel bad.

