He told me that you were his nephew.

1779
01:07:01,986 --> 01:07:03,055
Ms. Kim.

1780
01:07:03,056 --> 01:07:04,625
(Other happy faces)

1781
01:07:04,626 --> 01:07:06,425
- All three of them are teachers?
-  Yes.

1782
01:07:06,426 --> 01:07:07,526
- All three of them.
-  Yes.

1783
01:07:08,366 --> 01:07:09,366
Hello.

1784
01:07:09,367 --> 01:07:12,135
(The head of academic affairs, the principal)

1785
01:07:12,136 --> 01:07:14,536
Do you have food for yourselves?

1786
01:07:14,706 --> 01:07:15,765
- We have a lot.
-  We have plenty.

1787
01:07:15,766 --> 01:07:16,805
- Do you?
-  Too much, even.

1788
01:07:16,806 --> 01:07:18,335
- You have to make two rounds.
-  Really?

1789
01:07:18,336 --> 01:07:19,676
Yes. Come back for more.

1790
01:07:20,946 --> 01:07:23,506
Thank you. It looks so good.

1791
01:07:25,076 --> 01:07:26,815
- Hello.
-  Hi.

1792
01:07:26,816 --> 01:07:28,646
- Thanks for your work.
-  Hello.

1793
01:07:28,846 --> 01:07:31,255
Do the kids talk about the acting class?

1794
01:07:31,256 --> 01:07:32,256
They love it.

1795
01:07:32,257 --> 01:07:33,456
- Really?
-  Yes.

1796
01:07:33,786 --> 01:07:35,525
- Please enjoy.
-  Thank you.

1797
01:07:35,526 --> 01:07:37,696
- See you again.
-  Hello.

1798
01:07:38,396 --> 01:07:39,626
Everyone.

1799
01:07:39,856 --> 01:07:43,836
He's the chef who cooked for us today.

1800
01:07:44,066 --> 01:07:45,765
- Hello.
-  He's really famous.

1801
01:07:45,766 --> 01:07:46,935
Do you know him?

1802
01:07:46,936 --> 01:07:48,665
- We do.
-  Ahn Sung Jae.

1803
01:07:48,666 --> 01:07:50,436
- You're popular.
-  Gosh.

1804
01:07:52,006 --> 01:07:54,675
- Thank you for knowing me.
-  Why does he look so happy?

1805
01:07:54,676 --> 01:07:56,745
Of course, I do. Kids love me.

1806
01:07:56,746 --> 01:07:58,745
They all know you. You're popular.

1807
01:07:58,746 --> 01:08:02,346
He is Chef Ahn Sung Jae.

1808
01:08:02,516 --> 01:08:04,715
- Here, he's Whale Teacher.
-  Whale Teacher.

1809
01:08:04,716 --> 01:08:07,555
He's Whale Teacher because he looks like a whale.

1810
01:08:07,556 --> 01:08:09,855
Let's call him Whale Teacher, okay?

1811
01:08:09,856 --> 01:08:10,995
- Yes!
-  Yes!

1812
01:08:10,996 --> 01:08:13,965
It'll be lovely if you can thank Whale Teacher.

1813
01:08:13,966 --> 01:08:15,765
Should we say it together? One, two, three.

1814
01:08:15,766 --> 01:08:18,395
- Thank you, Whale Teacher.
-  Thank you, Whale Teacher.

1815
01:08:18,396 --> 01:08:19,765
You're welcome. Please enjoy.

1816
01:08:19,766 --> 01:08:21,835
- Please enjoy.
-  Thanks for the food.

1817
01:08:21,836 --> 01:08:23,705
- Thanks for the food.
-  We have plenty of food.

1818
01:08:23,706 --> 01:08:26,236
- You can have more if you want.
-  Yes.

1819
01:08:26,576 --> 01:08:28,506
- Let me try it.
-  Enjoy.

1820
01:08:28,546 --> 01:08:30,515
- Thank you for the food.
-  Thank you.

1821
01:08:30,516 --> 01:08:32,475
- Thank you.
-  You can have more if you want.

1822
01:08:32,476 --> 01:08:35,716
(Eating as soon as he was told to)

1823
01:08:37,156 --> 01:08:40,526
(An experienced noodle eater)

1824
01:08:41,856 --> 01:08:42,856
(Savoring)

1825
01:08:45,256 --> 01:08:46,725
(Amazed)

1826
01:08:46,726 --> 01:08:47,796
It's amazing.

1827
01:08:49,196 --> 01:08:51,695
(Going for the steak)

1828
01:08:51,696 --> 01:08:52,696
(Satisfied)

1829
01:08:52,697 --> 01:08:53,966
- It's Ahn Sung Jae.
-  What?

1830
01:08:55,136 --> 01:08:58,436
(Lastly, he tries the ham tangsuyuk.)

1831
01:08:59,936 --> 01:09:00,946
(For 3 consecutive times)

1832
01:09:03,346 --> 01:09:06,645
(Dipping generously in the sauce)

1833
01:09:06,646 --> 01:09:08,445
I love eating outside.

1834
01:09:08,446 --> 01:09:09,545
The classroom is...

1835
01:09:09,546 --> 01:09:11,585
- It tastes like a honey sauce.
-  Without that...

1836
01:09:11,586 --> 01:09:12,586
- Really?
-  Yes.

1837
01:09:12,587 --> 01:09:14,126
It's a persimmon sauce.

1838
01:09:14,986 --> 01:09:16,486
It tastes like honey.

1839
01:09:16,956 --> 01:09:19,095
- Really?
-  Does it taste like honey?

1840
01:09:19,096 --> 01:09:20,925
(The persimmon sauce is sold out.)

1841
01:09:20,926 --> 01:09:22,666
After eating this...

1842
01:09:23,766 --> 01:09:25,196
Don't you like it?

1843
01:09:25,496 --> 01:09:28,466
(They're mesmerized too.)

1844
01:09:28,806 --> 01:09:31,375
Gosh. The steak is so tasty. Try it.

1845
01:09:31,376 --> 01:09:33,306
You can sit here.

1846
01:09:33,636 --> 01:09:34,945
The steak tastes good.

1847
01:09:34,946 --> 01:09:36,075
Is the steak tasty?

1848
01:09:36,076 --> 01:09:37,646
Can you smell a smoky flavor?

1849
01:09:40,416 --> 01:09:42,115
Are you saying Kyung Mo's not skinny?

1850
01:09:42,116 --> 01:09:43,246
(The steak is sold out too.)

1851
01:09:45,356 --> 01:09:46,955
Why are your eyes so red?

1852
01:09:46,956 --> 01:09:48,925
(Savoring the broccolini too)

1853
01:09:48,926 --> 01:09:49,956
The meat?

1854
01:09:53,296 --> 01:09:54,795
- What are you doing?
-  I'm getting some more.

1855
01:09:54,796 --> 01:09:56,026
What? You're getting more?

1856
01:09:56,496 --> 01:09:57,665
Good.

1857
01:09:57,666 --> 01:09:58,696
Teacher.

1858
01:09:59,896 --> 01:10:00,936
Thank you.

1859
01:10:01,336 --> 01:10:03,266
(Teacher)

1860
01:10:04,006 --> 01:10:05,336
- Do you want more?
-  Yes.

1861
01:10:05,506 --> 01:10:06,975
- What?
-  What do you want?

1862
01:10:06,976 --> 01:10:08,305
- Pasta.
-  Pasta?

1863
01:10:08,306 --> 01:10:09,306
- Did you like the pasta?
-  Pasta...

1864
01:10:09,307 --> 01:10:10,675
- Give him.
-  and ham tangsuyuk.

1865
01:10:10,676 --> 01:10:12,046
Do you want more tangsuyuk too?

1866
01:10:13,016 --> 01:10:14,016
He's adorable.

1867
01:10:14,546 --> 01:10:16,746
You were the first to take the meal, so you get more first too.

1868
01:10:18,886 --> 01:10:20,215
(Getting ready for Round 2)

1869
01:10:20,216 --> 01:10:22,025
I'll finally eat.

1870
01:10:22,026 --> 01:10:23,285
- Enjoy.
-  Yes.

1871
01:10:23,286 --> 01:10:24,556
What is this? Whose is this?

1872
01:10:25,196 --> 01:10:26,626
Can I use it?

1873
01:10:27,266 --> 01:10:28,525
- Just use it.
-  What?

1874
01:10:28,526 --> 01:10:29,765
- "Just use it?" - Go for it.

1875
01:10:29,766 --> 01:10:30,796
(Go for it!)

1876
01:10:31,866 --> 01:10:33,635
(He's a cool boy who likes to eat.)

1877
01:10:33,636 --> 01:10:34,836
"Go for it."

1878
01:10:35,836 --> 01:10:38,205
- Thank you for the food.
-  Enjoy.

1879
01:10:38,206 --> 01:10:39,435
(North Pole Teacher finally takes a bite.)

1880
01:10:39,436 --> 01:10:40,475
It's good.

1881
01:10:40,476 --> 01:10:41,776
(North Pole Teacher finally takes a bite.)

1882
01:10:43,746 --> 01:10:44,945
- It's good, right?
-  Yes.

1883
01:10:44,946 --> 01:10:46,545
- Is it good?
-  It's good.

1884
01:10:46,546 --> 01:10:47,646
- Is it good?
-  Yes.

1885
01:10:49,946 --> 01:10:51,316
Is it tasty? What do you like the most?

1886
01:10:52,316 --> 01:10:53,556
- All of them.
-  All of them?

1887
01:10:54,186 --> 01:10:56,825
- What's your first pick?
-  What's your favorite?

1888
01:10:56,826 --> 01:10:58,156
(In charge of the steak)

1889
01:10:58,556 --> 01:10:59,655
First place is...

1890
01:10:59,656 --> 01:11:01,026
- Ham?
-  It's ham.

1891
01:11:01,926 --> 01:11:03,526
- This is in 2nd place.
-  Pasta is in 2nd place?

1892
01:11:03,626 --> 01:11:05,465
- What about the meat? The last?
-  In third place.

1893
01:11:05,466 --> 01:11:06,665
In third place? Okay.

1894
01:11:06,666 --> 01:11:07,836
(Pasta in 2nd, steak in 3rd)

1895
01:11:08,506 --> 01:11:10,836
(Laughing)

1896
01:11:11,836 --> 01:11:13,736
- Mr. Ahn.
-  Yes.

1897
01:11:14,576 --> 01:11:16,946
What was the tastiest dish you've ever had?

1898
01:11:19,516 --> 01:11:20,816
I've tried so many things.

1899
01:11:20,916 --> 01:11:24,556
Because my job is related to food,

1900
01:11:24,816 --> 01:11:26,056
I've had so many kinds of food.

1901
01:11:26,656 --> 01:11:27,956
I had so many dishes that I found tasty.

1902
01:11:28,056 --> 01:11:31,495
But what's memorable is what I ate when I was young.

1903
01:11:31,496 --> 01:11:32,725
- It's tasty.
-  Is this a pudding?

1904
01:11:32,726 --> 01:11:34,095
It would be the one my grandmother cooked.

1905
01:11:34,096 --> 01:11:35,126
(After eating all kinds of food around the world...)

1906
01:11:36,566 --> 01:11:38,666
- Potato tteok?
-  Potato tteok.

1907
01:11:38,896 --> 01:11:40,665
This is so tasty.

1908
01:11:40,666 --> 01:11:43,666
You taste food not only with your mouth but also with your heart.

1909
01:11:44,506 --> 01:11:45,506
It's tasty.

1910
01:11:45,507 --> 01:11:46,805
He said we taste the food with our hearts.

1911
01:11:46,806 --> 01:11:47,806
This is sweet.

1912
01:11:47,807 --> 01:11:49,705
If we say it's not tasty,

1913
01:11:49,706 --> 01:11:51,716
- Mr. Ahn will be sad.
-  That's right.

1914
01:11:52,076 --> 01:11:53,746
I'm used to it, though.

1915
01:11:54,786 --> 01:11:55,816
I'm strong on that side.

1916
01:11:56,086 --> 01:11:58,016
Until I've become who I am,

1917
01:11:59,786 --> 01:12:01,586
there were many people who told me it wasn't tasty.

1918
01:12:01,886 --> 01:12:04,725
But you just have to keep going with what you find right.

1919
01:12:04,726 --> 01:12:05,756
Do you want it?

1920
01:12:06,456 --> 01:12:07,465
Do you get it?

1921
01:12:07,466 --> 01:12:08,466
Yes.

1922
01:12:11,066 --> 01:12:12,765
- This is...
-  What is it?

1923
01:12:12,766 --> 01:12:14,936
(Stay strong and follow your own way.)

1924
01:12:16,366 --> 01:12:17,635
Let's try it.

1925
01:12:17,636 --> 01:12:20,076
- Why do I have two spoons?
-  I know.

1926
01:12:21,506 --> 01:12:23,445
I think so too.

1927
01:12:23,446 --> 01:12:24,545
- I have two spoons.
-  It happens.

1928
01:12:24,546 --> 01:12:26,346
Why? Why do you have two?

1929
01:12:27,016 --> 01:12:28,016
That's cool.

1930
01:12:29,646 --> 01:12:30,646
(Nodding to approve it)

1931
01:12:30,647 --> 01:12:31,986
The steak tastes amazing.

1932
01:12:33,916 --> 01:12:36,225
I was proud when we were eating together.

1933
01:12:36,226 --> 01:12:37,226
(How was cooking for the students?)

1934
01:12:37,227 --> 01:12:39,226
It was so worth it.

1935
01:12:39,526 --> 01:12:41,225
I'm not saying it...

1936
01:12:41,226 --> 01:12:42,466
because I cooked, and they liked it.

1937
01:12:42,966 --> 01:12:45,266
"What I had back then was unusual."

1938
01:12:45,466 --> 01:12:47,535
"How did they come up with that?"

1939
01:12:47,536 --> 01:12:50,566
If I made them curious, I'd say I was successful.

1940
01:12:51,806 --> 01:12:54,006
I don't expect all of them to feel that way.

1941
01:12:54,306 --> 01:12:56,145
If there's only one...

1942
01:12:56,146 --> 01:13:00,846
who goes, "There must be something more to it..."

1943
01:13:00,946 --> 01:13:02,046
with curiosity,

1944
01:13:04,186 --> 01:13:07,115
I've planted a seed in them.

1945
01:13:07,116 --> 01:13:09,626
(Hopefully the seeds will sprout one day.)

1946
01:13:10,586 --> 01:13:12,756
(Yongheung Elementary School Autumn Field Day)

1947
01:13:13,156 --> 01:13:14,466
(With the students' cheer,)

1948
01:13:14,896 --> 01:13:16,126
(they run,)

1949
01:13:16,526 --> 01:13:17,536
(scream with joy,)

1950
01:13:17,966 --> 01:13:19,636
(and show the best teamwork.)

1951
01:13:20,066 --> 01:13:22,536
(The whole school comes together.)

1952
01:13:23,636 --> 01:13:25,776
(And a cooking match with their pride at stake)

1953
01:13:26,306 --> 01:13:28,206
(How will Chef Ahn evaluate it?)

1954
01:13:28,476 --> 01:13:29,876
(It's undercooked.)

1955
01:13:30,706 --> 01:13:31,846
(It tastes bitter.)

1956
01:13:32,416 --> 01:13:34,346
(They're more serious than ever.)

1957
01:13:35,186 --> 01:13:38,916
(Who will Chef Ahn choose?)

1958
01:13:41,126 --> 01:13:44,155
(The OST of Curtain Up, Class!, "Best Scene" by DK)

1959
01:13:44,156 --> 01:13:50,996
(Available on all music streaming sites)

1960
01:14:20,573 --> 01:14:22,573
Dramaday.me
